author: leosimons
msg: Fix a nasty bug with dependency management right within the model.

* pygump/python/gump/model/__init__.py: Dependency up until now had an argument in __init__ that had a default value of []. That default value is created once, on subsequent invocations of __init__, the same list would be used. This effectively meant that all dependencies shared one global array of DependencyInfo, which of course is wrong, wrong, wrong.
